Words cannot explain how grateful we are for everyone who visited us yesterday. @beatsnbarsfest , @durhambulls and a @dpacnc Show all on campus @americantobaccocampus made for a record day and a challenging one for our kitchen which led to people waiting around 60-70 max wait times.

We apologize to anyone who was not happy with their experience. We are always open to feedback via DM or email at soulpatroldurham@gmail.com

Each challenging and busy service allows us the opportunity to learn and grow. We realize the challenge for our counter service/online and QR code business model is that we are not restricted by seats and may continue taking orders well past our small kitchen capacity. Table service restaurants for example, cannot seat more guests when they run out of seats and people are added to a waitlist in turn keeping the pace of orders to the kitchen manageable. During peak times, we may have to move to something similar in order to better manage the pace for our kitchen.

We thank you all again for constantly pushing us into new heights and challenges. We are forever grateful for you patience and understanding and again, if you were not happy with your experience please reach out and we will do what we can to make it right.

“This Boricua Soul Bowl 😮‍💨🔥🙌🏾
I usually keep my food reviews for Google, but I had to share this one on The Book!! Check out Boricua Soul, a Puerto Rican inspired soul food restaurant that’s LOVED by the Durham community!

Let’s get into this Boricua Soul Bowl! This bowl consists of a flavorful Puerto Rican-style slow roasted pork topped with pickled onions, pigeon peas and rice, vegan collard greens (VERY GOOD), mac and cheese, and fried plantain. EXCELLENT flavor through and through! Customer service was top notch! If you’re ever in the Bull City, be sure to stop by Boricua Soul! It is located at 705 Willard Street inside of the American Tobacco Campus.”
